LYDENDBURG &#8211; Twenty two people have been injured in an accident in the town. According to Netcare911 spokesman Ms Athlende Mathe, the accident occurred yesterday at 16:30.&#8220;One person was in a critical condition while the twenty one others sustained minor injuries.&#8221;She said a taxi and two bakkies had collided on the Roosenekal Road.Netcare911 paramedics worked alongside the Provincial EMS on scene.She said the person who was critical was stabilised and thereafter airlifted by the Provincial EMS to a nearby hospital for further medical care.